#rxvt clone with xft and unicode support

x11-terms/rxvt-unicode 256-color alt-font-width blink buffer-on-clear -fading-colors focussed-urgency font-styles iso14755 mousewheel perl -pixbuf secondary-wheel startup-notification unicode3 -vanilla wcwidth -xft

# 256-color		Enable 256 color support
# alt-font-width	Calculate the font using a different method
# blink			enable blinking text :D
# buffer-on-clear	Store visible output to history buffer when clearing screen with ctrl-l (see https://bbs.archlinux.org/viewtopic.php?id=129302)
# fading-colors		Enable colors fading when off focus
# focussed-urgency	Enable urgent flag when terminal window is focussed
# font-styles		Enable support for bold and italic fonts
# iso14755		Enable ISO-14755 support
# mousewheel 		Enable scrolling via mousewheel or buttons 4+5
# perl			Enalbe perl script support
# pixbuf		Enable transparency support using gtk's pixbuf
# secondary-wheel	Support for wheel scrolling on secondary screens (like mutt) (http://lists.schmorp.de/pipermail/rxvt-unicode/2011q4/001491.html)
# startup-notification	Enable application startup event feedback mechanism
# unicode3		Use 21 instead of 16 bits to represent unicode characters
# vanilla		Do not add extra patches wich change default behaviour
# wcwidth		Enable wide char width support
# xft			Build with support for XFT font renderer

